Certain - potentially they are quite decent Arkade races, but overall, the game is scattered by some unnecessary errors that are present in this series more or less for a few years.
So they are actually no mistakes anymore, but rather signs of a principally incomprehensible fault of the game developers.
The adventure begins very well.
For the first time one is introduced into the story, whose main character Jack has certain problems of personal character; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal racing throughout America.
In San Francisco, that is, on the west coast, you sit on the wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole number of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is held on a different track and that the individual stages are held in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
