Sometimes untypical elements bring a little variation into the individual races.
In the desert, for example, you are surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts the sight.
In the mountains again, you have to be careful that you are not scattered by a lavin.
At the same time, the individual races are well-established.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overcome the required number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to pick up (classic race against the stop hour), then you are waiting for another personal duel with a single opponent.
There is also a police officer who is trying to disguise the whole matter.
A new thing is passages in which Jack leaves the car.
It’s more about some interactive animations where Jack escapes from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right time.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are much less such passes in the game than you would expect (specially probably only three).
Finally, this is the thing rather to benefit, because so this element at least has no chance to get bored - it belongs in the context of the above to the elements that make the game more varied.
The driving model passes in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today’s point of view, though it doesn’t cut out trees, on the other hand, it could not be claimed to be bad.
Those who are looking for realistic simulations must look elsewhere.
But to an action-loaded race, the home driving model will continue to fit very well, although you could find better in the competition.
So far, everything is in the best order.
Real problems only arise after a certain time.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not completely OK.
From a game of this kind is hard to expect it to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have practically no explosion on any object knowing how the car behaves, then obviously not everything is fine.
A typical example: When closely riding or pre-driving on arrival cars, you “track” the other car easily in some places, but in other, almost identical situations you get into the slides and turn wild pirouettes.
Or the car runs down.
Thanks to the restart system, it doesn’t work any more, it’s annoying all the time.
The restarts are solved in this way: if you have total damage or land far from the track, then you throw the game back to the last point of the track.
Only - in each race you have only five restarts.
If you have spent it out, everything goes out from the front.
Therefore, the restarts are more like a help, for the event that something fails, but you should not rely on it.
But sometimes even restart doesn’t help, so nothing else helps but learning the critical section from the head.
Explicitly unpleasant is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, need to pass in a very specific way, otherwise you simply don’t fit through.
Otherwise, in the appropriate place you meet "civil" cars always in the same configuration, whether you come first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is annoying in situations when you see that the counterpart passes in front of a playing on two opposing cars, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to cross or brake them.
And it doesn’t matter when you get there, everything is designed so that this situation is always close to your nose.
The counterparts have other advantages.
Thro the game there are a few places where you are always overwhelmed at the same place by the same opponent and here again without regard to the time.
The most crazy is this to finish the game on the long bridge, which is passed in the opposite direction.
The opponent must surrender one here obviously to the devil.
And if he is already in front of one, then he naturally takes a look, so you start driving your own car in clump a few times.
Clearly - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting, but this intention is so clear that it quickly loses the joy of the game.
And that’s a pity, because despite the simpler driving model, the game is quite entertaining and sometimes so action-loaded that you almost don’t know where one of the heads is.
And, in principle, it doesn’t matter what’s “guilt” about it – the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no delusion can occur, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the car change during the races.
You should not ignore the tank stations on the route, because here you can change the car, although in most cases the car is enough that you are just having.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are good for the urban areas, the strong American limousines for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical trips, for example on the Serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the game history mode goes also the task mode (defiance) - that is, the races in the individual locations that you know from history.
Here there are not only medals, but also experience points to win for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (the challenges) and history.
To get to a higher driver level, different items must be opened: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is simultaneously associated with the online function Autolog, which, among other things, compares its own achieved results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of the other incomprehensible scratches is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you get by car to a subway tunnel (for me), where you get in the darkness on the railways (for me).
